    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UL config validation in NR UE scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE scheduler's `fill_ul_config` function was missing state validation before processing protocol messages downstream of the UL config clearing operation. This could lead to UL configurations being set for invalid slots when the frame/slot combination was not valid for UL transmission.\n\nThe issue occurred because after clearing the UL config for a new frame/slot (lines 109-110), there was no validation that the new frame_tx/slot_tx combination was actually valid for UL transmission before proceeding with protocol message processing (lines 118-123). This could result in UL configuration being set for invalid slots.\n\nThe fix adds explicit documentation of this requirement and an assertion to prevent exceeding maximum PDU limits.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_scheduler.c`: Added comment after clearing operation to document requirement for UL slot validation\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_scheduler.c`: Added assertion to validate maximum PDU count after incrementing\n\n"
}